<br>
2 points for 5% (cheap!)<br>
+4 points for +5% (total 10%) (exspensive!)<br>
+6 points for +10% (total 20%) (in between!)<br>
<br>
I've always assumed this meant something like, if I cast 5 sun vortexes in 30 seconds, but have subtlety 3, I will generate as much aggro as someone who casts 4 sun vortexes in 30 seconds without any subtlety. Another way to look at it, suppose you are &quot;Aggro-constrained,&quot; meaning, you have plenty of mana and there are lulls between your nukes, but if you nuked any more (i.e. shortened the lulls) you would steal aggro from the tank. Then the person with subtlety 3 can do about 20% more nuke damage (because of shorter lulls) then someone without. Actually, as the above example shows, it's closer to 25% more nuke damage. Compare this to SCF3, which is only roughly a 7% increase in damage (and not even that because it doesn't multiply focus bracer). OF course, to use the full 25% increase from subtlety, you have to use up 25% more mana. <br>
<br>
Notice the first level of subtlety is relatively inexpensive and easy to get (don't have to save up tons of points). I pretty much recomend everyone try to get at least the first level pretty quickly. In fact, if the prospect of saving up 6 points for SCM3 fills you with dread, the following starting order isn't too bad:<br>
<br>
run 3<br>
regen 3<br>
MC 1<br>
SCM 2<br>
subtlety 1<br>
ND 1<br>
 <p>Master Cydmab Promethean<br>
